### Implementation Guidance

**Follow GitHubRemotePreparation checklist** (Step 1-6):

**Step 1 - Create Repository**:
```bash
# Option A: GitHub Web UI
# Navigate to: https://github.com/new

# Option B: GitHub CLI (recommended)
gh repo create .xeyth --private --description "Lightweight AI instruction framework for agent-driven development"
```

**Repository Settings**:
- Name: `.xeyth`
- Description: `Lightweight AI instruction framework for agent-driven development`
- Visibility: Private
- Topics: `ai`, `framework`, `github-copilot`, `agent-driven-development`, `dotnet`, `vertical-slice-architecture`
- Initialize: ❌ NO (pushing existing repo)

**Step 2 - Configure Remote**:
```bash
# Replace {user} with GitHub username
git remote add origin https://github.com/{user}/.xeyth.git
git remote -v  # Verify
```

**Step 3 - Initial Push**:
```bash
git push -u origin master
```

**Step 4 - Verify**:
- [ ] Navigate to GitHub repository
- [ ] Verify README displays on landing page
- [ ] Check commit history (should show all local commits)
- [ ] Verify file structure matches local
- [ ] Confirm topics visible

**Step 5 - Next Steps** (document in Progress Log):
- Create Git/BranchProtectionRules.task
- Create Git/GitHubActionsWorkflows.task
- Create Git/AzureDevOpsIntegration.task
- Update Git/Repository.plan.Tasks.inventory

**Critical Notes**:
- Use GitHub CLI if available (`gh`) for automation
- Verify remote URL before pushing
- Check authentication (SSH vs HTTPS)
- Ensure working tree clean before push
- Document remote URL in task completion

